<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title> SOLE_PAIN_case_sheet_part</title>
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles.css" id="light-styles" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css" id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet"
      title="dark">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: SOLE PAIN (Plantar Foot Pain)</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>:
            Site</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="ortho-specific">HEEL (underside): <span class="ortho-specific">Plantar
                Fasciitis (most common), Fat Pad Atrophy, Calcaneal Stress
                Fracture</span></li>
            <li class="ortho-specific">ARCH: <span class="ortho-specific">Plantar
                Fasciitis, Posterior Tibial Tendon Dysfunction (flat foot)</span></li>
            <li class="cns ortho-specific">BALL OF FOOT (Forefoot): <span class="cns">Morton's
                Neuroma</span>, <span class="ortho-specific">Metatarsalgia</span>,
              <span class="ortho-specific">Stress Fracture</span>, <span class="rheumatic">Rheumatoid
                Arthritis</span></li>
            <li class="cns">DIFFUSE / RADIATING: <span class="cns">Tarsal
                Tunnel Syndrome, Lumbar Radiculopathy (S1)</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Can you point with one finger to the area of your
          sole that hurts the most?"</span></div>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>:
            Onset</span>
          <ul>
            <li>ACUTE / TRAUMATIC:
              <ul>
                <li class="ortho-specific">Rare for most conditions, but
                  possible Plantar Fascia rupture (audible pop)</li>
                <li class="rheumatic">Acute gout attack</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>GRADUAL / INSIDIOUS (No trauma):
              <ul>
                <li class="ortho-specific">Change in footwear, activity level,
                  or walking surface? (Plantar Fasciitis, Stress Fracture)</li>
                <li class="rheumatic">No preceding event? (Inflammatory
                  arthritis)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How did the pain start? Was there a specific
          injury, or did it come on gradually?"</span></div>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>:
            Duration</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How long has the sole of your foot been painful?"</span></div>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
            Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span>
          <ul>
            <li>AGGRAVATING: </li>
            <ul>
              <li class="ortho-specific">First steps in the morning, walking
                barefoot on hard surfaces (Plantar Fasciitis)</li>
              <li class="cns">Wearing narrow or high-heeled shoes (Morton's
                Neuroma)</li>
              <li>Prolonged standing or walking</li>
            </ul>
            <li>RELIEVING: </li>
            <ul>
              <li>Rest, supportive footwear/orthotics, calf stretches, ice</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"What makes the pain worse or better?"</span></div>
      <!-- C: Character -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
            Character</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="ortho-specific">SHARP / STABBING (especially with first
              steps): <span class="ortho-specific">Classic for Plantar
                Fasciitis</span></li>
            <li class="ortho-specific">DULL ACHE: <span class="ortho-specific">Stress
                fracture, arthritis</span></li>
            <li class="cns">BURNING / TINGLING / NUMBNESS: </li>
            <ul>
              <li class="cns"><span class="cns">Nerve involvement (<b><u>Morton</u></b>'s
                  Neuroma, Tarsal Tunnel, Radiculopathy)</span></li>
            </ul>
            <li class="cns">"LIKE A PEBBLE or folded <b><u>sock </u></b>in my
              shoe": <span class="cns">Classic for <b><u>Morton</u></b>'s
                Neuroma</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"What does the pain feel like? Is it a sharp
          stabbing, a dull ache, or burning?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Radiation -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
            Radiation</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="cns">Pain radiating from the back/buttock down the leg
              -&gt; Lumbar Radiculopathy</li>
            <li class="cns">Pain radiating from the forefoot into the toes -&gt;
              Morton's Neuroma</li>
            <li class="cns">Pain radiating from the inner ankle into the sole
              -&gt; Tarsal Tunnel Syndrome</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Does the pain travel anywhere, for example, up
          your leg or into your toes?"</span></div>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
            Associated Symptoms</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="ortho-specific">LOCAL SYMPTOMS
              <ul>
                <li class="ortho-specific">Mild swelling in the heel</li>
                <li class="cns">Clicking sensation in the forefoot when walking
                  (Mulder's Click - Morton's Neuroma)</li>
                <li class="rheumatic ortho-specific">Stiffness (especially
                  morning stiffness)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="General">SYSTEMIC / INFLAMMATORY SYMPTOMS
              <ul>
                <li class="infectious">Fever, chills (Infection - rare)</li>
                <li class="rheumatic">Pain or swelling in other joints (e.g.,
                  hands, wrists)?</li>
                <li class="rheumatic">Pain in other tendon insertion points
                  (enthesitis)?</li>
                <li class="rheumatic derma">Associated skin rashes (Psoriatic
                  Arthritis) or back pain (Ankylosing Spondylitis)?</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Besides the pain, have you noticed any swelling,
          stiffness, or other issues?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
            Progression</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Since it started, has the pain been getting
          better, worse, or staying the same?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
            Pattern</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="ortho-specific"><b>Worse with first steps in the morning
                or after a period of rest -&gt; Pathognomonic for Plantar
                Fasciitis</b></li>
            <li class="ortho-specific">Worse with increased activity / as the
              day goes on -&gt; Stress Fracture, Metatarsalgia</li>
            <li class="infectious ortho-specific oncology">Constant pain, worse
              at night, not relieved by rest -&gt; Red flag (Infection, Tumor,
              Nerve entrapment)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Is the pain worse at any particular time of day?"</span></div>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>:
            Effect on Life</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Limitation of walking distance</li>
            <li>Inability to participate in sports</li>
            <li>Need to modify footwear or activities</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How has this pain affected your ability to walk,
          work, or exercise?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
            Red Flags</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="infectious emergency">HOT, RED, SWOLLEN JOINT (e.g., big
              toe) -&gt; <b class="emergency">Septic Arthritis / Gout</b></li>
            <li class="cns emergency">NEW WEAKNESS (e.g., foot drop) or
              associated bladder/bowel changes with back pain -&gt; <b class="emergency">Cauda
                Equina Syndrome</b></li>
            <li class="oncology ortho-specific">SEVERE NIGHT PAIN, unexplained
              weight loss, history of cancer -&gt; <b class="emergency">Malignancy
                / Metastasis</b></li>
            <li class="ortho-specific">INABILITY TO BEAR WEIGHT after minimal
              trauma -&gt; <b class="emergency">Fracture</b></li>
            <li class="cns">BURNING PAIN, numbness, and color changes in a
              diabetic patient -&gt; <b class="emergency">Diabetic Neuropathy /
                Foot at risk</b></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"I need to ask some specific questions to make sure
          we're not missing anything serious."</span></div>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>:
            Severity / Scale</span> </div>
        <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how would you rate your
          pain right now, and at its worst?"</span></div>
    </div>
    <script src="harsha_iframe_youtube_player.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height_mothership.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height.js"></script>
    <script src="theme-toggle.js"></script>
    <script src="double_click_collapse_details.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
